MBOMBELA – Just over three years since the kidnapping and murder of Annatjie Myburgh from her home in Rocky Drift, on June 15, 2016, Selby John Mabila and Paul Mathebula were found guilty in the Mpumalanga Division of the High Court today. Her disappearance resulted in a large-scale search at the time, with the broader community getting involved in large numbers. ALSO READ: Double voting case in court They were further found guilty of robbery with aggravating circumstances as well as kidnapping. The case was postponed to August 15 for sentencing procedures. READ MORE: Annatjie Myburgh’s tragic end